y not be in the league of a mage or necro pet, but drop haste, dex and str on him and you have a permanent no-mana DOT. Plus he looks cute.<br><br>I hate shamans like you who insist on nuking every fight and then complain you're out of mana. Out DOTs are the greatest gift Verant ever gave us, and even in a fast-pulling group the poison ones are still well worth the casting. They're far more mana efficient than nukes.<br><br>I hate shamans like you who drop every buff known to man on the tanks at the start of the group, then complain you're OOM. /Selectively/ buff. And stagger the casting so you spread the different buffs out over 20 minutes. Plus cast them /all/ on yourself at the same time you do the tanks - it doesn't take that much mana, and you've got a timer for every buff - when it fades, reapply on everyone. A shaman who has to be asked to renew buffs is not doing his job, IMHO. Get your group used to the idea that they'll get the buffs, they don't have to whine for them. The next good shaman to group with this lot will bless you for training them well  <br><br>I hate shamans like you who 'won't cannibalise'. WHY NOT!!!! Cannibalise plus regen or even better chloroplast is the nearest you'll get to clarity without retraining as a chanter  <br><br>I hate shamans like you who haven't learned that while you may be the backup healer, in the absence of a chanter you are /far/ more use slowing the mobs, as it'll reduce the damage taken by the tanks ten times more then you could heal. Just keep that bit of mana for healis if it all goes pear shaped.<br><br>I hate shamans like you who don't do enough soloing to keep your weapon skills up. You are not a tank. But you can produce a damned good imitation if all else fails. You get decent AC. Use it.<br><br>I hate shamans like you, because it means that every time I group with a group who've had a bad shaman. they don't like me summoning a pet because he sucks mana, whine at me for every buff from the word go, panic if I cannibalise, and say they don't want me to apply any damage spell as I need the mana for heals, and don't dare let me tank even in an emergency because I &quot;can't take the aggro&quot;....<br><br>Shamans are one of the best classes in Norrath. And most shaman players are some of the best players in Everquest. So why, why, why must a small minority mess up things for the rest of us. Read. And learn.<br><br><br>Bronia Wolfdancer<br>Barbarian Shaman of the Tribunal<br>42nd Moon<br>Bloodsong <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umathii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mathii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/15/02 1:13:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1720.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I hate shamans like you...</span><hr size=1> lmao <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Good rant, even though it is somewhat close to telling people how to play their class.<br><br>If a person wants to be in a group without their defense maxed, buff till oom, have no pet, and not canni for mana...then let them die.  It's going to happen, and then they will learn <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center> <img src="http://cleric.homestead.com/files/oracle.jpg"> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> 