ave aggro and the tanks haven't caught it yet Slow and Nuke are our biggest taunts.<br><br>Buffs: Most groups I've been in complain if they don't have all the buffs they want as soon as I am in group. If I'm in a good group, I'm gonna be there for hours... and after the 3rd round the buffs are spread out. But I don't like spreading them too much.. then it feels like I am constantly buffing.  The timer is the best thing EVER. If for some reason I've gone LOM (hardly ever OOM) I let the tanks know that I don't have &lt;insert buff&gt; timed due to mana/battle constraints .. they always understand and I either refresh sooner or they let me know when it starts to drop.<br><br>Cannabalize and Slow: AGREE SO MUCH!<br><br>Weapons skill: If it comes down to me needed to tank a mob, I hope we are not relying on MY MELEE attacks to kill it. I can tank em pretty good, but a true tank is a meat shield not a damage dealer.<br><br>Groups with Bad Shaman experience: FUCK EM ... either tell them to do their job and you will do yours THE WAY YOU SEE FIT, find another group, or turn the damn tables on em.. tell the monk he can't pull for shit, tell the tank he should let the chanter be the meat shield because he's dieing too fast. ROFL its not the shaman's fault that some people are asses and have no clue how THAT DAMN GOOD we are!<br><br>ps, sorry for the length, but this hit the spot OH SO WELL.. everything I'd been thinkin for quite some time now.<br><br>/cheer Shaman!!!<br> <p><center><TABLE BACKGROUND="http://www.elltel.net/ethernexus/images/daback.jpg"BORDER="1"><TR><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><B><h4>Lelanie Frostspirit</h4><BR>Tribunal Shaman of the 49th Winter<BR>Assistant Guild Leader of the <A HREF="http://www.dragonsalliance.com"> Dragons Alliance</A>.<BR>"Bringing the Spirit to you,<br> cause the Frost is just too cold"<BR></B> <IMG SRC="http://www.elltel.net/ethernexus/images/medals/level40.gif"><IMG SRC="http://www.elltel.net/ethernexus/im