 use them every time.  If a mob needs to go down, fast, they go in.<br><br>BUFFS:  Yes, I try to time these.  The problem with timing buffs, however, is zones like Sebilis.  The froggies dispel.  A lot.  It is nothing to have the puller loose a couple buffs one pull, then have the primary tank loose a couple the next.  This complicates timing.  And the froggies <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> always</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> fucking dispel the most expensive spells first.  Never fails.<br><br>If people start getting dispelled, I don't time.  Period.  They either ask or they don't get it.  If they are too lazy to ask, they must not need it anyways.  (Believe me, a melee <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ask for a buff, if they feel its important.)<br><br>MELEE SKILLS:  LoL.  Unless I get my shaman a weapon <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> very</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> close to a 1/1 ratio (i.e. primal, NToV, or Ssra drop) I'm not even gonna try.  My little spine chill spear (10/2<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  doesn't do much to the mobs at 58.  I actually think the mobs laugh at me when I try to use it.  Can't see using a 2HB either, cuz I need the WIS and mana the spear + shield combo affords me.<br><br>As to what I define the shaman roles.  Well, in order of importantance:<br><br>1 - Debuffer:  Nothing is more important than getting a mob slowed, ASAP.  On named mobs, or anything with massive damage, I malosini first so slow--generally--will stick on the first try.  Sucks getting hammered by unslowed mobs.  Otherwise I just slow, and (if mana is holding good) I cripple.<br><br>2 - Crowd Control: After the mob is debuffed and pissed at me, I root park it somewhere away from the camp if I'm the crowd control.<br><br>3 - Buffer: Melee need STR and haste above everything.  Regeneration is the next priority.  After that, damage takers get stamina and agility.  Casters get stamina and Kragg if they want it.  Dexterity and charisma are luxury spells; they only get cast if asked for (I don't work with chanters or bards often enough to remember using charisma).<br><br>4 - Damage:  If mana is good, the party is buffed, and the mobs are debuffed I might land an ebolt or plague.  Never before I've buffed/debuffed though.<br><br>Petting has a priority on my list between buffing and damage, if I plan to use one, though generally I do not.  Pets, to me, are just a pain in the ass.  Maybe when I get /pet HOLD I'll change my mind, but until then... /pet get lost.<br><br>Beyond that... *shrug*.  I think its a moot point.  Each to their own.  What I do works for me.  What other shaman do works for them.  If they aren't getting a group killed, just leave 'em the fuck alone. <p>Shallandra McKnight, Uba Monkey<br>Zassazy Moonkiepett, Sexy Leezard Shaman<br>Daxes Solvaires, Naughty Flute Girl<br>Daemonica, Evil Daughter of Innoruuk<br><br>"Train?  What train?!!  There are ONLY twelve of them!"</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showMessageRange?topicID=1720.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showPrevMessage?topicID=1720.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showNextMessage?topicID=1720.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1720.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsa